      },
      "date": "2013-11-16 06:40:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThe problem with this patch is that 020000000 is not also conflicting with O_TMPFILE IN 3.11 so it makes sense to figure out what value we will use for the new O_LOV_DELAY_CREATE flag and add it into this patch as well. One option is O_NOCTTY, which should never conflict in the future.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "26351b631b70e8f34d08e912d9384e8a949d1985",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-11-16 07:34:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI'm not against landing this patch to b2_1, but I'd also like to get a fix for LU-4209 landed to b2_1as well (as a separate patch), so that there is more forward compatibility for apps in case O_TMPFILE is also backported to older kernels. \n\nI'm rejecting this patch because it should follow proper formatting of the commit comment for backported patches. Best would be to cherry-pick the original commit ae9ad4db so it has the original LU-812 ticket number in the commit summary line, the original Author:, Recvewed-by: and Signed-off-by: lines (remove the Change-Id: line and Tested-by: lines) and then add:\n\n Lustre-commit: ae9ad4db69ea04b9bbfb929a390e75f6a506aa79\n Lustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/3779\n\nThis makes it much easier to see that this is the same patch as was landed for LU-812.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
